&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Advanced Nurse Practitioner role in Cardiology has been developed to ensure seamless delivery of care from referral throughout the patient pathway within the Cardiology Directorate of the Oxford University Hospitals. The post holder will work with the Lead Nurse to lead and develop services including pre-admission clinics, nurse-led discharge policies and be involved in cardiology clinics where appropriate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work closely with Matron, Consultant Nurse, Lead Nurse, ward managers, cardiology medical staff and a team of senior staff nurses within the Cardiology directorate to provide clinical support, education and clinical leadership to the development of the patient pathway. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;‘A highly experienced, knowledgeable and educated member of the team who is able to work autonomously making high level decisions to treat health needs.’ Advanced level practice encompasses aspects of education, research and management but is firmly grounded in direct care provision or clinical work with patients’ families and populations’&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. (CNO 2010)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planned interview: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKatie KonstanciakJob titleCardiology Lead NurseEmail addressKatie.Konstanciak@ouh.nhs.ukTelephone number01865 572667Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are recommended prior to interview.&lt;/p&gt;
